.SH NAME
.PP
monospace-cache - Manage the monospace task cache


.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\fBmonospace cache [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Manage the task cache used to skip unchanged tasks during pipeline execution.

.PP
Cache entries are stored in .monospace/.cache/ inside the monospace root.
A task uses the cache when its pipeline entry sets cache: "skip" or cache: "restore".


.SH OPTIONS
.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for cache


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
